In a speech to the United Nations General Assembly, Foreign Minister Valid al-Mualem said conditions were improving in the country.
"Today, the situation on the ground is more stable and safer, which is due to the progress made in the fight against terrorism," he said.
The government continues to rebuild areas devastated by terrorists in order to bring the situation back to normal.
All conditions for the voluntary return of refugees to the country they had to leave due to terrorism and unilaterally introduced economic measures that had an impact on their daily lives and lives have now been ensured.
The UN estimates that more than 5.5 million Syrians have fled the country since the start of the war in 2011.
An additional six million people living in the country are in need of humanitarian assistance.
Al-Mualem said the Syrian regime welcomes assistance in rebuilding the devastated country.
But he stressed that he would not accept conditional aid or aid from the countries that sponsored the uprising.
